pma:database.name: camprecon
pma:database.pma:table: CREATE TABLE `tblcourse` ( `strCourseID` varchar(10) NOT NULL, `strCourseName` varchar(25) NOT NULL, `strDepartment` varchar(25) NOT NULL, `strGenEdCategory` varchar(3) NOT NULL, `strPrerequisite` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL, `strCorequisite` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL, `intCredits` int(1) NOT NULL, `dblFee` float NOT NULL, `strCourseDescription` varchar(140) DEFAULT NULL ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `tblfacility` ( `intFacilityID` int(7) NOT NULL, `strFacilityName` varchar(64) NOT NULL, `strStreet` varchar(32) NOT NULL, `strCity` varchar(16) NOT NULL, `strState` varchar(2) NOT NULL, `strPostCode` varchar(9) NOT NULL, `intLongitude` float NOT NULL, `intLatitude` float NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`intFacilityID`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `tblfaculty` ( `intFacultyID` int(7) unsigned NOT NULL, `strLastName` varchar(24) NOT NULL, `strFirstName` varchar(24) NOT NULL, `strMiddleName` varchar(24) NOT NULL, `strDepartment` varchar(20) NOT NULL, `strPosition` varchar(15) NOT NULL, `blnAdvisor` varchar(1) NOT NULL, `strFacultyEID` varchar(24) NOT NULL, `intSecurityGroup` int(3) NOT NULL ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `tblsection` ( `intSectionID` int(12) NOT NULL, `strCourseID` int(10) NOT NULL, `strRoomID` int(5) NOT NULL, `intFacultyID` int(7) NOT NULL, `intTimeSlotID` int(3) NOT NULL, `intYear` int(4) NOT NULL, `strSeason` int(8) NOT NULL, `dtmStart` timestamp NOT NULL, `dtmEnd` timestamp NOT NULL, `intCapacity` int(3) NOT NULL, `intWaitlistTotal` int(3) NOT NULL, `blnOnlineSection` tinyint(1) NOT NULL, `strRequiredText` varchar(25) NOT NULL ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `tblstudent` ( `intStudentID` int(7) unsigned NOT NULL, `intFacultyID` int(7) unsigned NOT NULL, `strFirstName` varchar(24) NOT NULL, `strLastName` varchar(24) NOT NULL, `strMiddleName` varchar(24) DEFAULT NULL, `strStatus` varchar(8) NOT NULL, `strEnrollmentStatus` varchar(8) NOT NULL, `strStudentType` varchar(3) NOT NULL, `strMajor1` varchar(20) NOT NULL, `strMajor2` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL, `strMajor3` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL, `strMinor1` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL, `strMinor2` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL, `strMinor3` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL, `dblGPA` float DEFAULT NULL, `intCredits` int(3) DEFAULT NULL, `blnActiveService` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL, `intSecurityGroup` int(3) NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`intStudentID`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `tblstudentenrollment` ( `intStudentID` int(7) NOT NULL, `intSectionID` int(12) NOT NULL, `dblSectionGrade` float DEFAULT NULL, `strEnrollmentStatus` varchar(1) DEFAULT NULL, `strPermitStatus` varchar(1) DEFAULT NULL, `intWaitlistPosition` int(3) DEFAULT NULL ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `tblusercontact` ( `intContactID` int(7) NOT NULL, `intExternalID` int(7) NOT NULL, `strCountry` varchar(15) DEFAULT NULL, `strStreet` varchar(15) DEFAULT NULL, `strCity` varchar(15) DEFAULT NULL, `strState` varchar(2) DEFAULT NULL, `strPostCode` varchar(9) DEFAULT NULL, `intMobileNumber` int(11) DEFAULT NULL, `intHomeNumber` int(11) DEFAULT NULL, `intEmergencyNumber` int(11) DEFAULT NULL, `strEmergencyContactType` varchar(15) DEFAULT NULL, `strEmergencyContactLastName` varchar(24) DEFAULT NULL, `strEmergencyContactFirstName` varchar(24) DEFAULT NULL, `blnEmergencyContact` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL, `blnMailingAddress` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL, `blnPermanent` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;
